## Possible Angles

### 1. Golf/Sports Lifestyle Brand Extension
*If LazyGolf becomes a recognizable brand...*

**Concept:** "LazyGolf Mobile" - cell service for the golf lifestyle
- Golf course coverage prioritized
- Course finder/GPS included
- League chat features built-in
- Discounts on golf apps/services

**Challenges:** Very niche, may not justify MVNO complexity

### 2. Family/Elder-Focused
*Ties into Rent-a-Nerd tech support...*

**Concept:** Cell service designed for seniors/tech-challenged
- Simplified plans (one option, not 50)
- Built-in tech support (unlimited help)
- Family dashboard for remote assistance
- Large-button phone options

**Opportunity:** Real pain point, existing competitors (Lively, Consumer Cellular)

### 3. Privacy-Focused
**Concept:** No tracking, no data selling, privacy-first mobile
- Minimal data collection
- No selling customer data
- Transparent privacy policy
- Premium pricing justified by privacy

**Challenge:** Technical complexity of actually delivering this

### 4. Developer/Tech Community
**Concept:** Mobile service for developers
- API access to your account
- Detailed usage analytics
- Multiple SIMs per account easy
- Testing/sandbox numbers

**Opportunity:** Underserved, willing to pay more

